                    <msContents>
                        <summary>This Arabic <title>Muʻallaqāt</title> (Suspended Odes) by seven
                            pre-Islamic Arabic poets, allegedly written on cloth then displayed upon
                            the Ka‘bah contains an anonymous interlinear Persian translation and
                            commentary. Complete, albeit unsigned and undated, an unidentified
                            scribe copied it on British-manufactured handmade paper watermarked
                                    <watermark><q>J. Bigg</q></watermark> manufactured by <placeName
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7461984" key="place_7461984"
                                >Iping, West Sussex</placeName> papermaker <persName role="ppm"
                                key="">John Bigg (fl. 1746–1772)</persName>, which indicates the
                            manuscript must date roughly to the third quarter of the 18th
                            century.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_137559-item1">
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20324" change="#ids-cleanup"
                                >Muʻallaqāt</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar">المعلقات</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20324" change="#ids-cleanup"
                                >Muʻallaqāt al-Saba‘</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_20324" change="#ids-cleanup">المعلقات
                                السبع</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="supplied">The Mu'allaqāt</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ
                                    (folio 1b):</locus> و هذة الطبقة الا و هی السموط و... </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="ar"><locus from="135a" to="135a"> برگ ۱۳۵ر (folio
                                    139b):</locus> شیخی الفتی اعداء و یعقر جارة. </explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="fa">No colophon.</colophon>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                            <author key="person_15146522404232391917"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/15146522404232391917/">
                                <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Imruʼ al-Qays,
